    "## 9. Optimum selection — direct conservative-margin search (NSGA-II-free)\n",
    "\n",
    "The three mechanical responses are collinear, so the multi-objective front degenerates and an evolutionary search (NSGA-II) is unnecessary. We select directly over space-filling Sobol candidates: $i^*$ maximises the conservative LINEX margin $\\delta^\\star_M=\\mathbf{c}^\\top\\boldsymbol{\\mu}-\\tfrac{a_M}{2}\\mathbf{c}^\\top\\boldsymbol{\\Sigma}\\mathbf{c}$ ($a_M=1.5$); $\\hat{\\imath}$ is a TOPSIS cross-check. Confirmation (Sec 7) uses representative configurations of this regime where physical replicates exist."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 13,
   "id": "2b00c569",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "predicted-response correlation over the box: r12=0.99 r23=0.98 r13=0.95\n",
      "-> strongly collinear: no trade-off among mechanical responses; NSGA-II not needed.\n",
      "\n",
      "operating point (direct conservative-margin search) + TOPSIS cross-check:\n",
      "  i*    : layer 0.127  temp 223.8  infill 29.7  speed 61.2  |  modulus 568  strength 20.93  SED 4.765\n",
      "  TOPSIS: layer 0.127  temp 223.8  infill 29.7  speed 61.2  |  modulus 568  strength 20.93  SED 4.765\n",
      "-> TOPSIS coincides with i* (collinearity): a single optimum, no separate MCDM point.\n",
      "   (i' in the confirmation study is an independent high-infill CONTRAST, not an optimum.)\n"
     ]
    }
